history.text: Hi! So what did you think about the Initiation Game?
*Imitation
I really liked it! how about you?
Same here! It was great drama, in my opinion. So who was your favorite character? Mine was Alan!
Alan was great, but I favored Keira Knightley's character Joan. Do you think the chronological order of these fictitious characters being changed altered the dynamics of the story?
I do agree Keira's character Joan was great! It is really hard for me to honestly say in terms of the characters changing the dynamics of the story. What about you?
I don't know how the events historically unfolded but i'm guessing from the document provided they did not happen in such an dramatic way.
Do you find Cumberbatch eccentric?
Cumberbatch's portrayal of Alan Turing that is.
I found he had a natural array of eccentricities.... I Did feel he was the highlight of the film. How about you?
I think some of his actions may have been exaggerated for dramatic affect. Do you normally watch drama films?
I do, not often, but occasionally.  I enjoy drama and biopics like The Imitation Game - especially those that are beautifully written, elegantly mounted and poignantly performed.
How did the relationship between Turing and Morcom make you feel?
I thought it was very sweet and heartbreaking in the end when he died of tuberculosis before Turing could confess his love. How about you?

I also think it is sad. Do you think it was coincidence that Turing's love for cryptography makes it his
 destiny to solve the enigma?
I think so honestly. That Enigma Machine was fascinating! How about you?

Even if it wasn't his knowledge could not have been better used. How many people were in the cryptography
 team?
I believe 5. I know it consisted of Hugh, John, Peter, Keith and Charles...
Who is the director?
How did you feel about Turing naming the machine "Christopher"?
The director was Morten Tyldum. I thought Morten did a fantastic job directing!
I thought it was quirky to name it after his crush.
Did you realize Turing was gay before the flashback to his school days?
I actually didn't realize that he was until he confessed it to Cairncross. What about you?
No it was a total surprise.
What year was this movie made
Agreed! How did you feel about Turing discovering  Cairncross was actually a Soviet spy? I was shocked!
It was released in 2014!
Why can't they act on the decoded messages from the enigma?
It was because the Germans would have realized Enigma had been broken.

What was the metacritic score and do you think that it was a accurate representation of the mo
vie.

It was 73/100 and I feel it maybe should have been a little higher. I enjoyed the fact that there were twists, such as Menzies already knowing Cairncross was a Soviet spy and and planted him among them for British benefits. That was a surprise to me.
I thought the Rotten Tomatoes score was more accurate.
How did you feel about the story overall? I thought Graham Moore did a brilliant job writing the story based on the biography written by Andrew Hodges.
